modules.description: Encodes and decodes byte sequences using the COBS algorithm to ensure no occurrence of a specified delimiter, typically 0x00, enabling reliable packet framing in binary streams. Processes raw byte arrays and returns encoded or decoded byte sequences with error handling for invalid input. Useful for real-time communication protocols where packet boundaries must be clearly defined without relying on special characters.

Encodes and decodes byte sequences using the COBS (Consistent Overhead Byte Stuffing) algorithm, handling zero-byte delimiters and ensuring no trailing delimiter in the output. Operates on OCaml's bytes type, preserving raw binary data integrity during encoding and decoding. Used to prepare data for transmission over protocols that require byte-stuffing, such as serial communication or custom binary formats.
